The paper deals with stochastic optimization methods, which are commonly used in machine learning and optimization problems. The focus is on reducing variance in online optimization, which is a key problem in the field of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also deals with optimization methods for deep learning architectures, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
